Description: 24/7 Technology is a providers of critical power solutions.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: 24/7 Technology is unique in the UPS service and maintenance industry due to the comprehensive range of services we provide in our corporate office.  Our facility, just outside of Atlanta, Georgia, incorporates administration, training, repair, logistics, and equipment inventory under one roof. Our capabilities include a full 3 phase 800A service for our test bays where we refurbish, repair and test single and three phase UPS's from 3KVA to 1000KVA. In house load banks and battery strings allow us to fully test our systems in all operational modes. Component level diagnostic and repair capabilities are also available in our corporate office. Our UPS training facility offers a formal classroom curriculum covering UPS power electronics, theory, service, and a wide range of topics from the National Electrical Code® (NEC) to interfacing with generators, PDU's, and monitoring systems. Once formal classroom training is completed, new engineers are trained on operation, troubleshooting, and maintainence using actual equipment that we have in-house. Our warehouse stocks UPS's from all manufacturers in all sizes including accessories such as PDU's, battery cabinets and racks, maintenance bypass panels, and of course new batteries for immediate emergency response or nationwide shipping. We also stock a wide range of UPS spare parts including circuit boards, power supplies, fans, circuit breakers, semi conductors, fuses and capacitors. Our people and our infrastructure enable us to consistently deliver world class service to our customers. We are looking forward to the opportunity to serve you!

Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: XpenseWise is a marketing platform for banks to improve their ability to cross-sell bank products to their existing customer base. In an era when it seems that everyone is competing for a piece of the financial institution pie, XpenseWise can help you strengthen your ties to your customers, meeting a greater share of their financial needs. XpenseWise works by analyzing data from a user's household bills. They get this data either automatically, as they pay bills online with your EBPP (electronic bill presentment and payment) service, or directly from the user, via fax or manual input. XpenseWise also gathers preference and credit data to build a complete user history. Financial institutions can use this data base to identify customers' bank product holdings and needs, and effectively cross-sell them additional bank products. XpenseWise uses the database to match user's histories to better value offers in the marketplace for non-bank products such as long distance, cell phone, insurance, etc. Users love the savings they get with XpenseWise, and will thank you for bringing the service to them. Protecting your customer's privacy is part of their reason for being. Users must opt-in to use XpenseWise. And, they act as an infomediary, using consumers' data to their advantage in finding them better offers, but NEVER selling data or identifying a user to a third party vendor.

Description: Pinky’s Kitchen was founded in November 2011 by Australian born chef and entrepreneur Andrew Bray.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Using only the highest quality ingredients, hours of smoking it to perfection, handcrafting their award winning sauce, and providing the best customer service...that is their philosophy here at Pinky's Kitchen. Pinky’s Kitchen was founded in November 2011 by Australian born chef and entrepreneur Andrew Bray. Pinky’s acknowledges the personal nature of BBQ and people’s strong allegiances to the regional styles of BBQ they grew up with. What is comfort food for one man can be adventurous eating to the next. Seattle being a diverse city of transplants Pinky’s draws upon what it considers to be the best methods and techniques of slow smoking its dry rubbed meats using locally sourced Applewood which provides a distinctly Pacific Northwest flavor. Bray has developed a line of unique BBQ sauces most using smoked onions and garlic as a base and which represent the major American states of BBQ. All their sides are scratch made using quality ingredients and modernized versions of the classics. Specialty meats can be smoked at request and essentially all sorts of surprises can pop up as specials on the menu as Pinky’s follows the simple rules of “if it tastes good it is good” and refuses to remain bound by the confines of any single tradition.
